content.description:
This was formerly known as the "Off-width of Death", but upon actually climbing it there's good pro all the way and FUN chimney climbing at the top with a jug top out that goes at 5.9. 

  Follow the nice crack left of Best Jams to a pod in the Chimney with a no hands rest. Plug bomber gear and thrash to the apex of the roof and plug a #5 C4 to protect the top out.
content.protection: Finger and hand sized. Save a #5 C4 for the very top. TR is east to set off some trees.

content.description: Crux at the top after the large jug. May be a scary lead going between bolt 1 and 2.

climbs.name: Clinical Procedure
climbs.fa: (potentially) Gokul Gopal and members of the Outdoor Adventure Club from Platteville

content.description: P1 (5.5, 35'): Climb the hand crack that goes up two feet right of the arete, to a ledge with a big tree. You can walk off left from here, if desired.P2 (5.8, 55'): Move the belay back on the ledge system to the base of a slabby block. Go up the slab to a tight dihedral. The crux is near the top of the dihedral. Top out onto the ledge system above, head to the short wall then climb up by a sandy crack (about 3 feet left of a tree that stands close to the wall).Descent: Walk (or rap from a tree) off from the summit.
content.location: This is at the very north (i.e., left) end of the Amphitheater Wall, just around the corner from the Incredible Hulk area.

content.description: Obvious crack that widens at the top. No real defined crux, just continuous jams all the way to the top.
content.protection: Cams only .75-4 , use chain anchors as for neighboring sport route
content.location: Left of the bolted line, on the right end of the ampmhitheater.

content.description: Large amphitheater just south of the Rusted Ring wall. Route are primarily on the far right end of it.
